Emergency paramedics wearing a full COVID-19 coronavirus personal protective equipment (PPE) transfer an empty gurney to an ambulance at the Greenacres Hospital in Port Elizabeth, on July 10, 2020. JOHANNESBURG - Deaths due to COVID-19 in South Africa have surpassed 21,000. The health department recorded 2,493 new COVID-19 cases in the country in the last 24 hours. READ: NMB hospitals overwhelmed with COVID-19 surge The death toll now stands at 21,083 after 115 more people died of COVID-19. The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases is 772,252. Recoveries now stand at 716,444 which translates to a recovery rate of 92.8-percent. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs